As a part-time undergraduate student and a member of the Association of Part-time Undergraduate Students (APUS), you are connected with thousands of students locally, provincially and nationally.You are also a member of the global student movement that continues to be at the forefront of change, challenging systems of oppression both on and off our campuses.

To get involved with your student movement, volunteer with APUS! Fill out the application in our bio or scan the QR code. We are excited to have you join APUS and are looking forward to connecting during our events! 

For any questions, please email vpoutreach@apus.ca!

Your students’ union and the student movement have won countless victories for you! 

Many perks we enjoy at UofT—from securing part-time seats on university committees to eliminating out-of-province fees for Indigenous students—are the result of relentless student advocacy and organizing. The student movement has also organized and lobbied for the implementation of sexual violence prevention policies in post-secondary institutions across the province. Students have fought hard to achieve these victories and we don’t plan to stop anytime soon. 

Want to get involved in the student movement? Check out our last post for more information!

As part-time students, we get that connecting can be difficult, especially because we’re spread across three campuses. But don’t worry—APUS got you!🤪

From Orientation and Welcome Back Week to Cupcake and Chill, Board Games and Destressors, we’ve got events all year long to bring part-time students together. Whether you need to de-stress during exams or just want to hang out, there’s always something happening at APUS. 

This year we’re excited to be hosting a mix of in-person and virtual events so stay tuned because you don’t want to miss out. Orientation and welcome week events details coming soon!👀

At APUS, we get it—being a student is expensive. That’s why your student union offers a range of cost-saving services all year long!

Drop by the APUS Student Service Centre (ASC) in Sid Smith Building, Room 1089, for cheap printing, a cozy hangout spot, and events that help you connect with other part-time students. 🖨️☕️But that’s just the start!

From a free discount card (ISIC) to our Health and Dental program, bursaries, academic support, and more, we’re here to make sure you have access to the resources you need to have a well rounded and supportive post-secondary education experience.

For any questions please email vpinternal@apus.ca!

Part-time students face systemic barriers and challenges while accessing post-secondary education. As the central students’ union representing part-time undergraduates, we are committed to confronting these injustices and challenges. We organize and lobby at the local, provincial, and national levels to ensure students have access to free and accessible post-secondary education and a just future. 

From Fight the Fees to Fairness for International Students to Consent is Mandatory to Students Against War, we are here to firmly oppose all systemic injustices while creating anti-oppressive spaces and ensure we continue to represent you - the students. Keep an eye out this year for our upcoming campaigns and organizing series, activist assemblies and workshops!

For any questions, please email vpexternal@apus.ca!

Welcome to your part-time undergraduate students’ union!☺️

The Association of Part-Time Undergraduate Students (APUS) is your central part-time students’ union. We’re here to ensure that all part-time students have a holistic university experience! 

As an APUS member, you can access all of our campaigns, services, and events! Through these three main pillars, we ensure that part-time students have a supportive and enriching undergraduate journey. 

Keep an eye out for the following posts to learn more about your students’ union, the three pillars, and all the perks of being an APUS member. We will wrap up the series by letting you know how you can join the student movement and get more involved with APUS!

OISE Grad Students – Health & Dental Opt-Out Info! 🦷🩺

🚨 Opt-Out Deadlines:
Fall Change-of-Coverage Period: Sept. 5 - 30, 2024
Winter Change-of-Coverage Period: Jan. 6 - 31, 2025 (for new January students)

Eligibility to Opt-Out:
You can opt out if you're covered by an equivalent health and/or dental plan (like a parent’s or spouse’s plan).
Proof of Coverage: You must show proof of other health and/or dental coverage to opt out.

Valid Period: Opt-outs are valid from Sept. 1, 2024 – Aug. 31, 2025. You’ll be automatically re-enrolled next year if you return as an eligible student.

📲 Refund Info: After your opt-out is processed, you'll receive a refund via email money transfer or direct deposit once the Change-of-Coverage Period ends.

Where: MP408
Time: 5pm onwards 

Speaker: Vivek Dhande 

Abstract:
Quantum physics introduces a new paradigm in computing hardware, allowing quantum computers (QC) to promise computational speed-ups for a unique set of challenging problems. This talk will cover two leading QC hardware platforms: transmons & SQUIDs in superconducting QC and quantum dots (QDs) in semiconducting QC. Vivek will also explore research in 3D integration of superconducting resonators for charge sensing readout of Ge QDs using flip-chip technology, as well as atomistic simulation of production CMOS Si spin-qubit devices in 22nm FDSOI. Finally, he will highlight key global players and ecosystems driving QC advancement today. Three key sectors will be in focus: scientific progress in academia, industrial adoption for utility-scale commercialization, and government support via grants, programs, and legislation.
